org.chronos.chronodb.api.key

Interface ChronoIdentifier

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ChronoIdentifierImpl

    public interface ChronoIdentifier
    A ChronoIdentifier is a TemporalKey with additional metadata.

    Every entry in the entire ChronoDB can be uniquely identified by a ChronoIdentifier.

    This class does not extend TemporalKey or QualifiedKey due to problems with collection containment checks and the #equals(Object) method.

      • toTemporalKey

        TemporalKey toTemporalKey()
        Returns a representation of this ChronoIdentifier as a TemporalKey.

        Note that a TemporalKey contains less data than a ChronoIdentifier. Two different identifiers may therefore produce two equal temporal keys.

        Returns:
        The temporal key representation of this identifier. Never null.

      • toQualifiedKey

        QualifiedKey toQualifiedKey()
        Returns a representation of this ChronoIdentifier as a QualifiedKey.

        Note that a QualifiedKey contains less data than a ChronoIdentifier. Two different identifiers may therefore produce two equal qualified keys.

        Returns:
        The qualified key representation of this identifier. Never null.
